The paper focuses on improving the quality of synthesized images in GANs, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. The proposed U-Net based discriminator architecture is inspired by segmentation literature, which is also a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) research. The paper also introduces a new data augmentation technique, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. The paper discusses the quality of generated images, which is related to graphics (cs.GR) research. Finally, the paper mentions the use of datasets such as FFHQ, CelebA, and COCO-Animals, which are commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
